        How Recycling Helps <span>Fight Climate Change?</span>
    </h1>
    <p>
        Recycling helps to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by reducing the need for virgin materials. Here’s how recycling combats climate change:
    </p>
    <ul type="disc">
        <li>
            <h3>Energy Savings: </h3>
            Recycling aluminum, for instance, saves up to 95% of the energy required to make new aluminum from bauxite.
        </li>
        <li><h3>Low Carbon Footprints: </h3>Recycling paper and plastics instead of producing new ones cuts down on the carbon emissions that contribute to global warming.</li>
        <li><h3>Conserves Resources: </h3>By reusing materials, recycling reduces the environmental impact of mining and extraction processes, which are carbon-intensive.</li>
    </ul>
